having everything,

264
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:30,133
you actually have nothing.

265
00:17:31,533 --> 00:17:33,267
You are alone in life.

266
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:40,933
I'm out.

267
00:17:42,567 --> 00:17:44,867
Where are you going?

268
00:17:44,933 --> 00:17:47,333
Does it hurt to
hear the truth?

269
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:50,367
I hate to tell you this
but it's time for you to go.

270
00:17:50,467 --> 00:17:53,300
Stop using this community
service as an excuse for Mikoy

271
00:17:53,367 --> 00:17:57,233
to love you again
and your whole family.

272
00:17:57,300 --> 00:17:59,333
They were happy even
if you're not here.

273
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:02,533
And they will continue
to be happy even if you leave.

274
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:07,600
Get off me!

275
00:18:10,033 --> 00:18:12,067
You are really a witch!

276
00:18:24,767 --> 00:18:27,400
Do you like it?

277
00:18:27,467 --> 00:18:28,700
This is really good.

278
00:18:32,033 --> 00:18:34,433
I prepared it myself.

279
00:18:34,500 --> 00:18:36,667
I know that when it comes
to adobo,

280
00:18:36,733 --> 00:18:41,000
you like yours dry and oily.

281
00:18:42,733 --> 00:18:44,700
You've really perfected this.

282
00:18:44,767 --> 00:18:47,733
And that's one thing
that really impresses me.

283
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:50,400
If there's one thing
that you want to learn...

284
00:18:50,467 --> 00:18:52,567
you become really,
really good at it.

285
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:56,400
And if I remember correctly...

286
00:18:56,500 --> 00:18:58,933
when we got married,
you don't know how to cook.

287
00:19:03,667 --> 00:19:05,667
Okay, keep walking.

288
00:19:05,733 --> 00:19:08,200
Keep walking...

289
00:19:08,267 --> 00:19:10,567
and stop.

290
00:19:10,633 --> 00:19:12,067
Surprise!

291
00:19:20,033 --> 00:19:21,533
Sorry, Hon.

292
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:23,867
That's only what I can cook.

293
00:19:26,767 --> 00:19:28,367
It looks nice.

294
00:19:28,467 --> 00:19:29,867
Come on, let's eat.

295
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:36,300
Go ahead.

296
00:19:42,100 --> 00:19:43,167
Come on.

297
00:19:53,100 --> 00:19:54,233
There you go.

298
00:19:54,300 --> 00:19:55,333
Thank you.

299
00:19:58,333 --> 00:20:00,567
Get some more.

300
00:20:00,633 --> 00:20:02,167
Later.

301
00:20:02,267 --> 00:20:03,400
Okay, thanks.

302
00:20:09,467 --> 00:20:11,600
I was shocked
that you ate everything

303
00:20:11,667 --> 00:20:14,000
that I cooked that day.

304
00:20:14,067 --> 00:20:16,333
I can still remember your face.

305
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:18,300
You know,
you were trying so hard

306
00:20:18,367 --> 00:20:20,500
to look like
you're not affected...

307
00:20:20,567 --> 00:20:22,267
but I could sense

308
00:20:22,333 --> 00:20:26,000
that you want to vomit
everything that you eat.

309
00:20:26,067 --> 00:20:29,400
Yes, I can vividly
remember that day.

310
00:20:30,967 --> 00:20:34,033
My stomach was so upset
the whole day in the office.

311
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:40,467
You know, I can endure the burnt
fried egg or hotdog,

312
00:20:40,567 --> 00:20:44,933
but my stomach almost turned
upside down to the fried rice

313
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:47,400
that swims in oil.

314
00:20:47,467 --> 00:20:50,100
I'm so sorry.

315
00:20:50,167 --> 00:20:51,333
Oh my God.

316
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:56,400
That day I have to admit,
I learned I was a bad cook.

317
00:20:56,467 --> 00:20:59,033
I don't know anything.

318
00:20:59,100 --> 00:21:01,100
But you know what
I realized more?

319
00:21:03,467 --> 00:21:04,833
You really are a good guy.

320
00:21:05,867 --> 00:21:08,100
You never made me feel bad...

321
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,400
or inadequate.

322
00:21:10,667 --> 00:21:12,167
And for that I'm thankful.

323
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:18,933
To a life without regret.

324
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:20,800
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

325
00:21:27,600 --> 00:21:28,567
Eat some more.

326
00:21:39,633 --> 00:21:40,633
Delicious.

327
00:21:42,500 --> 00:21:44,133
Don't side with me.

328
00:21:46,100 --> 00:21:47,833
You should side with Hazel.

329
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:51,067
In fact to be honest...

330
00:21:52,233 --> 00:21:53,733
I was just being unfair.

331
00:21:57,267 --> 00:21:59,333
I was unfair to her
because of you.

332
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:00,433
Huh?

333
00:22:00,500 --> 00:22:03,667
Wait.

334
00:22:03,733 --> 00:22:05,367
Why?

335
00:22:05,433 --> 00:22:07,033
What's my fault?

336
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:12,567
Seriously?

337
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:15,700
You don't know...

338
00:22:15,800 --> 00:22:17,133
what you did to me?

339
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:20,367
So what is this I feel?

340
00:22:20,433 --> 00:22:21,633
Imagination?

341
00:22:27,767 --> 00:22:31,067
Tell me what my fault is.

342
00:22:31,133 --> 00:22:33,533
You have the nerve to say
that between the two of us,

343
00:22:33,600 --> 00:22:36,267
I'm the one who gave up on us.

344
00:23:00,500 --> 00:23:01,433
You're leaving?
- Why?
- Nothing.

345
00:23:02,500 --> 00:23:05,033
I can stay here.

346
00:23:05,100 --> 00:23:07,833
I'm sure
you will come back to me.

347
00:23:07,900 --> 00:23:10,533
You're not a good fit
for Celeste.

348
00:23:10,600 --> 00:23:13,767
Do you think
she still likes Mikoy?

349
00:23:13,833 --> 00:23:15,967
That's really what I feel.

350
00:23:16,033 --> 00:23:18,267
You're jealous of Celeste.

351
00:23:19,833 --> 00:23:21,000
You shouldn't have done that.

352
00:23:21,067 --> 00:23:23,167
You should grant my request
because this is the last.

353
00:23:34,300 --> 00:23:37,467
Do you regret now
that you kissed me?

354
00:23:39,367 --> 00:23:40,367
Hazel...

355
00:23:41,933 --> 00:23:43,567
someone wants
to talk to you.
